    <string name="jail_card_help_title">What Jail can and can\u2019t do</string>
    <string name="jail_card_help_subtitle">Plain expectations: what this feature can help you with, and what it does not change.</string>
    <string name="jail_help_title">About Jail</string>
    <string name="jail_help_can_title">What Jail can do</string>
    <string name="jail_help_can_body">• Guide you to reduce what a selected app can see and do (permissions, background work, network path through a chosen WireGuard tunnel).\n• Help you think in terms of work profile separation and pre-launch checklists — not a technical bypass of the Android sandbox.</string>
    <string name="jail_help_cannot_title">What Jail cannot do</string>
    <string name="jail_help_cannot_body">• It does not make a third-party app \u201Csafe\u201D or \u201Cuntrackable\u201D. The app can still see what you do inside it and can use any permission you grant.\n• It does not block in-app tracking, overlay fraud, or all fingerprinting. A VPN changes the network path, not every way an app can infer state.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_progress_format">Step %1$d of %2$d</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_title">Work profile guide</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_next">Next</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_back">Back</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_done">Done</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_what_title">What is a work profile?</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_what_body">A work profile is a separate space on your device with its own app installs and data. It is created by Android or your organisation — Jail cannot create it for you.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_detect_title">Check whether you already have one</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_detect_body">Look for a briefcase badge on app icons, or open Android Settings and search for \u201CWork profile\u201D. Jail can detect that another profile exists, but cannot always confirm its exact type. If nothing exists, use Settings \u2192 Accounts (or your IT instructions) to add one — not from this screen.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_install_title">Apps are installed separately</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_install_body">Putting an app \u201Cin work\u201D means installing it again inside the work profile. Jail does not move or clone app data automatically.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_icons_title">Choose the right icon</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_icons_body">The icon with the briefcase launches the work-profile copy; the normal icon launches the personal profile copy. They are separate installations.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_limits_title">What isolation helps with</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_limits_body">Work profile reduces exposure of personal apps and files to the work copy. It does not stop the app from observing what you do inside that app.</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_honest_title">Honest limits</string>
    <string name="jail_wizard_step_honest_body">This wizard is guidance only. Your employer\u2019s MDM or Android\u2019s own settings control provisioning. Jail shows status when it can — it does not promise automated setup.</string>
