    <string name="jail_detail_routing_help_body">Jail routing edits the include/exclude app lists on the tunnel you picked as the Jail tunnel (same lists as the Routing tab). Jail merges your choice with what is already there; if the tunnel is in the wrong split-tunnel mode (include-only vs exclude-only), Android cannot merge automatically — switch mode in Routing, or pick another tunnel.</string>
    <string name="jail_merge_confirm_title">Merge Jail routing?</string>
    <string name="jail_merge_confirm_body">This updates the chosen tunnel\u2019s per-app routing lists. Existing entries from the Routing tab are preserved where possible; Jail only removes entries it previously added when you clear a Jail routing mode.</string>
    <string name="jail_detail_routing_merge_tunnel_message">This updates \"%1$s\" include/exclude lists. Entries from the Routing tab stay merged; Jail only removes packages it previously managed when you revert a Jail policy.</string>
